history.content:
If you're already at 16 units (if I understand correctly), then you can't take another 4 unit course (if that's what you're trying to do). You can only enroll or waitlist in 1.5 more units of courses during Phase 2.

---------------------------------

The point of a 17.5 unit phase 2 is so that you can enroll in classes like seminars (1 unit) or PE classes (0.5 units). Also, if you have some weird combination of 3-unit, 4-unit, and 5-unit classes, it's pretty helpful.

Hi, 

I'm trying to phase 2 some CS classes (186, 189, 161) so I can hopefully get into one of them when the spring semester begins. I added 186 successfully, but trying to add more than 4 units gives me the "Unit exceeded for appointment" error. 

I thought we could enroll in 17.5 units for phase 2? Does L&S cap me at 16 units for the time being (currently enrolled and waitlisted in a total of 16 units right now)? In that case, what's the point of having a 17.5 unit phase 2?

Thanks
history.subject: Unit exceeded for appointment period
